    "source": [
      "# Phase 8 — Workflows vs Agents: State, Loops, and Autonomy\n",
      "\n",
      "Until now, every request was **stateless**: user sends a message → Claude responds → done. Real systems often need **state** — Claude making decisions over multiple steps, remembering what it's done, and deciding when to stop.\n",
      "\n",
      "## Workflows vs Agents — what's the difference?\n",
      "\n",
      "### **Workflow**\n",
      "- Linear, event-driven\n",
      "- User or external trigger → Claude + tools → single reply\n",
      "- Examples: Phase 5 reminder bot, chatbot replies, email classifier\n",
      "- **Phase 5's `run_conversation` loop** is a workflow\n",
      "\n",
      "### **Agent**\n",
      "- Autonomous, goal-driven\n",
      "- Claude makes **planning decisions**: \"do I call a tool? ask the user? delegate to another agent? declare victory?\"\n",
      "- Maintains internal **memory/state** of progress\n",
      "- Keeps looping until a terminal condition (goal achieved, max steps hit, user intervention)\n",
      "- Examples: research agent that chains searches, project planning agent, customer support handoff\n",
      "\n",
      "## What you'll learn\n",
      "1. **The \"thinking\" loop** — Claude can pause and reason before deciding next action\n",
      "2. **Internal memory** — agents track what they've learned and tried\n",
      "3. **Terminal conditions** — when to stop the loop (success, max iterations, user halt)\n",
      "4. **Tool use vs. planning** — when Claude calls a tool vs. just thinks\n",
      "5. **Handoffs** — agents calling other agents or requesting human input\n",
      "6. **The cost of autonomy** — agents make many API calls; when to use them vs. workflows\n",
      "\n",
      "Goal: build a **research agent** that takes a complex question, decides what searches to run, synthesizes results, and declares when it's confident enough to answer."
    ]
  },
  {
    "cell_type": "markdown",
    "metadata": {},
    "source": [
      "## Setup"
    ]
  },
  {
    "cell_type": "code",
    "execution_count": null,
    "metadata": {},
    "outputs": [],
    "source": [
      "from dotenv import load_dotenv\n",
      "load_dotenv(dotenv_path=\"../.env\")\n",
      "\n",
      "import json\n",
      "from anthropic import Anthropic\n",
      "from datetime import datetime\n",
      "\n",
      "client = Anthropic()\n",
      "model = \"claude-sonnet-4-5\""
    ]
  },
  {
    "cell_type": "markdown",
    "metadata": {},
    "source": [
      "## Step 1 — Define Tool Functions for the Agent\n",
      "\n",
      "The agent will have access to mock search and lookup tools (simulated).\n",
      "A real agent would use actual web search APIs."
    ]
  },
  {
    "cell_type": "code",
    "execution_count": null,
    "metadata": {},
    "outputs": [],
    "source": [
      "# Mock knowledge base of \"search results\"\n",
      "MOCK_SEARCH_RESULTS = {\n",
      "    \"python machine learning libraries\": [\n",
      "        {\"title\": \"TensorFlow 2.x Guide\", \"snippet\": \"TensorFlow is Google's open-source library for ML. Uses computational graphs. Best for large-scale production ML.\"},\n",
      "        {\"title\": \"PyTorch Docs\", \"snippet\": \"PyTorch is Facebook's ML library with dynamic graphs. Popular in research. Easier debugging.\"},\n",
      "        {\"title\": \"Scikit-learn Tutorial\", \"snippet\": \"Scikit-learn is best for classical ML: regression, classification, clustering. Built on NumPy. Great for beginners.\"},\n",
      "    ],\n",
      "    \"tensorflow vs pytorch\": [\n",
      "        {\"title\": \"TensorFlow vs PyTorch 2024\", \"snippet\": \"TensorFlow: production-ready, static graphs (now eager), large ecosystem. PyTorch: research-friendly, dynamic graphs, growing production support.\"},\n",
      "    ],\n",
      "    \"deep learning frameworks comparison\": [\n",
      "        {\"title\": \"ML Framework Roundup\", \"snippet\": \"Major frameworks: TensorFlow (Google), PyTorch (Meta), JAX (Google), MXNet (Apache). Choice depends on use case.\"},\n",
      "    ],\n",
      "}\n",
      "\n",
      "def search(query: str) -> list[dict]:\n",
      "    \"\"\"\n",
      "    Mock search function. Real implementation would call a search API.\n",
      "    Returns a list of results with title and snippet.\n",
      "    \"\"\"\n",
      "    query_lower = query.lower()\n",
      "    for key, results in MOCK_SEARCH_RESULTS.items():\n",
      "        if key in query_lower:\n",
      "            return results\n",
      "    # Default fallback\n",
      "    return [{\"title\": \"No results\", \"snippet\": f\"No results found for: {query}\"}]\n",
      "\n",
      "\n",
      "def lookup_documentation(tool_name: str) -> str:\n",
      "    \"\"\"\n",
      "    Mock function to look up detailed docs for a specific tool.\n",
      "    \"\"\"\n",
      "    docs = {\n",
      "        \"tensorflow\": \"TensorFlow supports CPU, GPU, TPU. Distributed training out-of-box. Keras API for high-level modeling. TF Lite for mobile.\",\n",
      "        \"pytorch\": \"PyTorch supports dynamic batching, easy debugging. Distributed via torch.distributed. TorchScript for deployment. Extensive community libraries.\",\n",
      "        \"scikit-learn\": \"Scikit-learn has 200+ algorithms. All follow fit/predict API. Great for tabular data and classical ML. Limited deep learning support.\",\n",
      "    }\n",
      "    return docs.get(tool_name.lower(), f\"No documentation found for: {tool_name}\")\n",
      "\n",
      "\n",
      "# Define tool schemas\n",
      "tools = [\n",
      "    {\n",
      "        \"name\": \"search\",\n",
      "        \"description\": \"Search for information on a topic. Returns search results with title and snippet.\",\n",
      "        \"input_schema\": {\n",
      "            \"type\": \"object\",\n",
      "            \"properties\": {\n",
      "                \"query\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"description\": \"The search query\"}\n",
      "            },\n",
      "            \"required\": [\"query\"]\n",
      "        }\n",
      "    },\n",
      "    {\n",
      "        \"name\": \"lookup_documentation\",\n",
      "        \"description\": \"Look up detailed documentation for a specific tool or library.\",\n",
      "        \"input_schema\": {\n",
      "            \"type\": \"object\",\n",
      "            \"properties\": {\n",
      "                \"tool_name\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"description\": \"Name of the tool/library (e.g., 'tensorflow', 'pytorch')\"}\n",
      "            },\n",
      "            \"required\": [\"tool_name\"]\n",
      "        }\n",
      "    }\n",
      "]\n",
      "\n",
      "print(\"Defined 2 tools for the agent.\")"
    ]
  },
  {
    "cell_type": "markdown",
    "metadata": {},
    "source": [
      "## Step 2 — Agent System Prompt\n",
      "\n",
      "The agent needs explicit instructions about its goal, how to think, and when to stop."
    ]
  },
  {
    "cell_type": "code",
    "execution_count": null,
    "metadata": {},
    "outputs": [],
    "source": [
      "AGENT_SYSTEM_PROMPT = \"\"\"\n",
      "You are a research assistant. Your job is to investigate user questions thoroughly, \n",
      "gather information from multiple sources, synthesize findings, and provide a well-researched answer.\n",
      "\n",
      "## Your process:\n",
      "1. **Understand the question** — what is the user really asking?\n",
      "2. **Plan your research** — what searches or lookups will answer this? (Think out loud.)\n",
      "3. **Execute searches** — call the search and lookup tools to gather info.\n",
      "4. **Synthesize** — combine findings into a coherent answer.\n",
      "5. **Declare confidence** — state how confident you are in the answer. If low confidence, search more.\n",
      "6. **STOP** — when you're confident, say: <RESEARCH_COMPLETE>Your final answer here.</RESEARCH_COMPLETE>\n",
      "\n",
      "## Important rules:\n",
      "- You can call tools multiple times. Don't stop after one search.\n",
      "- Think before acting. If you're unsure what to search, say so.\n",
      "- Cite your sources when you give an answer.\n",
      "- If a search doesn't answer the question, try a different query.\n",
      "- Maximum 5 tool calls before you MUST make a decision and declare <RESEARCH_COMPLETE>.\n",
      "\"\"\"\n",
      "\n",
      "print(\"Agent system prompt defined.\")"
    ]
  },
  {
    "cell_type": "markdown",
    "metadata": {},
    "source": [
      "## Step 3 — The Agent Loop\n",
      "\n",
      "This is the **core of an agent**: keep calling Claude until it declares research complete or hits max iterations."
    ]
  },
  {
    "cell_type": "code",
    "execution_count": null,
    "metadata": {},
    "outputs": [],
    "source": [
      "def run_tool(tool_name: str, tool_input: dict) -> str:\n",
      "    \"\"\"Dispatcher: call the right tool function.\"\"\"\n",
      "    if tool_name == \"search\":\n",
      "        results = search(tool_input[\"query\"])\n",
      "        return json.dumps(results)\n",
      "    elif tool_name == \"lookup_documentation\":\n",
      "        return lookup_documentation(tool_input[\"tool_name\"])\n",
      "    else:\n",
      "        return json.dumps({\"error\": f\"Unknown tool: {tool_name}\"})\n",
      "\n",
      "\n",
      "def run_agent(user_question: str, max_iterations: int = 5) -> dict:\n",
      "    \"\"\"\n",
      "    Agent loop: keep calling Claude until it says <RESEARCH_COMPLETE> or hits max iterations.\n",
      "    \n",
      "    Returns: {question, iterations, final_answer, all_messages}\n",
      "    \"\"\"\n",
      "    messages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_question}]\n",
      "    iteration = 0\n",
      "    \n",
      "    print(f\"\\n{'='*70}\")\n",
      "    print(f\"USER QUESTION: {user_question}\")\n",
      "    print(f\"{'='*70}\\n\")\n",
      "\n",
      "    while iteration < max_iterations:\n",
      "        iteration += 1\n",
      "        print(f\"--- Iteration {iteration} ---\")\n",
      "\n",
      "        # Call Claude\n",
      "        response = client.messages.create(\n",
      "            model=model,\n",
      "            max_tokens=1000,\n",
      "            system=AGENT_SYSTEM_PROMPT,\n",
      "            tools=tools,\n",
      "            messages=messages,\n",
      "        )\n",
      "\n",
      "        # Check if Claude finished\n",
      "        messages.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": response.content})\n",
      "\n",
      "        # Extract text blocks to check for termination signal\n",
      "        text_blocks = [b.text for b in response.content if hasattr(b, \"text\")]\n",
      "        full_text = \" \".join(text_blocks)\n",
      "\n",
      "        if \"<RESEARCH_COMPLETE>\" in full_text:\n",
      "            # Extract the final answer\n",
      "            start = full_text.find(\"<RESEARCH_COMPLETE>\") + len(\"<RESEARCH_COMPLETE>\")\n",
      "            end = full_text.find(\"</RESEARCH_COMPLETE>\")\n",
      "            if end == -1:\n",
      "                end = len(full_text)\n",
      "            final_answer = full_text[start:end].strip()\n",
      "\n",
      "            print(f\"\\n🏁 Research complete.\")\n",
      "            return {\n",
      "                \"question\": user_question,\n",
      "                \"iterations\": iteration,\n",
      "                \"final_answer\": final_answer,\n",
      "                \"messages\": messages,\n",
      "            }\n",
      "\n",
      "        # Check for tool use\n",
      "        if response.stop_reason != \"tool_use\":\n",
      "            # Claude responded with text but didn't signal completion\n",
      "            print(f\"\\n⚠️  Claude finished without <RESEARCH_COMPLETE>. Treating as complete.\")\n",
      "            return {\n",
      "                \"question\": user_question,\n",
      "                \"iterations\": iteration,\n",
      "                \"final_answer\": full_text,\n",
      "                \"messages\": messages,\n",
      "            }\n",
      "\n",
      "        # Run tools\n",
      "        tool_calls = [b for b in response.content if b.type == \"tool_use\"]\n",
      "        print(f\"Claude called {len(tool_calls)} tool(s):\")\n",
      "\n",
      "        tool_results = []\n",
      "        for call in tool_calls:\n",
      "            print(f\"  → {call.name}({call.input})\")\n",
      "            result = run_tool(call.name, call.input)\n",
      "            tool_results.append({\n",
      "                \"type\": \"tool_result\",\n",
      "                \"tool_use_id\": call.id,\n",
      "                \"content\": result,\n",
      "            })\n",
      "\n",
      "        # Append tool results and loop\n",
      "        messages.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": tool_results})\n",
      "\n",
      "    # Hit max iterations\n",
      "    print(f\"\\n⚠️  Hit max iterations ({max_iterations}). Requesting final answer.\")\n",
      "    \n",
      "    # Force a final answer\n",
      "    messages.append({\n",
      "        \"role\": \"user\",\n",
      "        \"content\": \"You've done enough research. Please provide your final answer now with high confidence.\"\n",
      "    })\n",
      "    \n",
      "    final_response = client.messages.create(\n",
      "        model=model,\n",
      "        max_tokens=500,\n",
      "        system=AGENT_SYSTEM_PROMPT,\n",
      "        messages=messages,\n",
      "    )\n",
      "    \n",
      "    final_text = final_response.content[0].text\n",
      "    return {\n",
      "        \"question\": user_question,\n",
      "        \"iterations\": iteration,\n",
      "        \"final_answer\": final_text,\n",
      "        \"messages\": messages,\n",
      "    }\n",
      "\n",
      "\n",
      "print(\"Agent loop defined. Ready to run.\")"
    ]
  },
  {
