      "## Step 5 — Compare: Workflow vs Agent\n",
      "\n",
      "### Workflow (from Phase 5)\n",
      "- Single turn or conversation-driven\n",
      "- User tells Claude what to do\n",
      "- Claude executes (reminder bot: get time, add days, set reminder)\n",
      "- Done\n",
      "\n",
      "### Agent (this phase)\n",
      "- Goal-driven\n",
      "- Claude decides WHAT to search and WHY\n",
      "- Loops until confident or max iterations\n",
      "- Can adapt strategy mid-stream\n",
      "\n",
      "Let's show the difference side-by-side:"
    ]
  },
  {
    "cell_type": "code",
    "execution_count": null,
    "metadata": {},
    "outputs": [],
    "source": [
      "print(\"\"\"\n",
      "╔════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n",
      "║               WORKFLOW vs AGENT — Key Differences                  ║\n",
      "╠════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n",
      "║                          WORKFLOW          │          AGENT        ║\n",
      "╠═══════════════════════════════════════════╪═════════════════════════╣\n",
      "║ Decision making        │ User decides      │ Claude decides       ║\n",
      "║ Loop termination       │ Single turn       │ Until goal achieved  ║\n",
      "║ Memory/state           │ Message history   │ Internal planning    ║\n",
      "║ Tool strategy          │ Prescribed        │ Autonomous choice    ║\n",
      "║ API calls              │ Few (1-3)         │ Many (up to 10+)     ║\n",
      "║ Complexity             │ Simple, linear    │ Complex, adaptive    ║\n",
      "║ Cost                   │ Low               │ Higher (more calls)  ║\n",
      "║ When to use            │ Well-defined task │ Vague/complex goal   ║\n",
      "║ Example                │ Reminder bot      │ Research assistant   ║\n",
      "╚═══════════════════════════════════════════╧═════════════════════════╝\n",
      "\"\"\")"
    ]
  },
  {
    "cell_type": "markdown",
    "metadata": {},
    "source": [
      "## Step 6 — Agent with Memory (Optional State)\n",
      "\n",
      "Agents can maintain explicit memory of what they've learned. Let's extend the agent to track findings."
    ]
  },
  {
    "cell_type": "code",
    "execution_count": null,
    "metadata": {},
    "outputs": [],
    "source": [
      "def run_agent_with_memory(user_question: str, max_iterations: int = 5) -> dict:\n",
      "    \"\"\"\n",
      "    Extended agent that tracks what it's learned in an explicit memory dict.\n",
      "    \"\"\"\n",
      "    messages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_question}]\n",
      "    memory = {\"findings\": [], \"confidence\": 0}\n",
      "    iteration = 0\n",
      "\n",
      "    while iteration < max_iterations:\n",
      "        iteration += 1\n",
      "        print(f\"\\n--- Iteration {iteration} ---\")\n",
      "        print(f\"Current findings: {len(memory['findings'])}\")\n",
      "        print(f\"Confidence: {memory['confidence']}/10\")\n",
      "\n",
      "        # Call Claude with memory in the context\n",
      "        memory_context = f\"\"\"\n",
      "Your current research memory:\n",
      "- Findings so far: {len(memory['findings'])}\n",
      "- Confidence level: {memory['confidence']}/10\n",
      "- Key findings: {', '.join(memory['findings'][:3]) if memory['findings'] else 'None yet'}\n",
      "\"\"\"\n",
      "\n",
      "        system_with_memory = AGENT_SYSTEM_PROMPT + \"\\n\" + memory_context\n",
      "\n",
      "        response = client.messages.create(\n",
      "            model=model,\n",
      "            max_tokens=800,\n",
      "            system=system_with_memory,\n",
      "            tools=tools,\n",
      "            messages=messages,\n",
      "        )\n",
      "\n",
      "        messages.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": response.content})\n",
      "        text_blocks = [b.text for b in response.content if hasattr(b, \"text\")]\n",
      "        full_text = \" \".join(text_blocks)\n",
      "\n",
      "        # Update memory from Claude's reasoning\n",
      "        if \"confidence\" in full_text.lower():\n",
      "            # Simulate confidence extraction (in practice, you'd parse this more carefully)\n",
      "            memory[\"confidence\"] = min(10, memory[\"confidence\"] + 2)\n",
      "\n",
      "        # Check for completion\n",
      "        if \"<RESEARCH_COMPLETE>\" in full_text:\n",
      "            start = full_text.find(\"<RESEARCH_COMPLETE>\") + len(\"<RESEARCH_COMPLETE>\")\n",
      "            end = full_text.find(\"</RESEARCH_COMPLETE>\")\n",
      "            if end == -1:\n",
      "                end = len(full_text)\n",
      "            final_answer = full_text[start:end].strip()\n",
      "            return {\n",
      "                \"question\": user_question,\n",
      "                \"iterations\": iteration,\n",
      "                \"final_answer\": final_answer,\n",
      "                \"memory\": memory,\n",
      "            }\n",
      "\n",
      "        # Run tools\n",
      "        if response.stop_reason != \"tool_use\":\n",
      "            return {\n",
      "                \"question\": user_question,\n",
      "                \"iterations\": iteration,\n",
      "                \"final_answer\": full_text,\n",
      "                \"memory\": memory,\n",
      "            }\n",
      "\n",
      "        tool_calls = [b for b in response.content if b.type == \"tool_use\"]\n",
      "        tool_results = []\n",
      "\n",
      "        for call in tool_calls:\n",
      "            result = run_tool(call.name, call.input)\n",
      "            tool_results.append({\n",
      "                \"type\": \"tool_result\",\n",
      "                \"tool_use_id\": call.id,\n",
      "                \"content\": result,\n",
      "            })\n",
      "            # Record the finding\n",
      "            memory[\"findings\"].append(f\"{call.name}: {call.input}\")\n",
      "\n",
      "        messages.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": tool_results})\n",
      "\n",
      "    return {\n",
      "        \"question\": user_question,\n",
      "        \"iterations\": iteration,\n",
      "        \"final_answer\": \"Max iterations reached.\",\n",
      "        \"memory\": memory,\n",
      "    }\n",
      "\n",
      "\n",
      "print(\"Agent with memory defined.\")"
    ]
  },
