    "source": [
      "## Step 7 — When to Use Agents vs Workflows\n",
      "\n",
      "| Scenario | Use Workflow | Use Agent |\n",
      "|----------|-------------|----------|\n",
      "| Task is well-defined (e.g., \"set a reminder\") | ✅ | ❌ |\n",
      "| Task is vague and exploratory | ❌ | ✅ |\n",
      "| User specifies exact steps | ✅ | ❌ |\n",
      "| Claude must decide what to search | ❌ | ✅ |\n",
      "| Cost is critical (low API call budget) | ✅ | ❌ |\n",
      "| User tolerates latency (multi-second) | Both OK | ✅ |\n",
      "| Real-time chat interface | ✅ | ❌ |\n",
      "| Background research task | ❌ | ✅ |\n",
      "| Multi-step problem solving | ❌ | ✅ |\n",
      "| Risk of hallucination (needs verification) | ❌ | ✅ |\n",
      "\n",
      "## Common Pitfalls with Agents\n",
      "\n",
      "1. **Infinite loops** — no terminal condition, agent keeps searching forever\n",
      "   - Fix: set `max_iterations`, require `<RESEARCH_COMPLETE>` signal\n",
      "\n",
      "2. **Tool thrashing** — agent calls same tool repeatedly, learning nothing new\n",
      "   - Fix: track what's been searched, guide Claude toward new queries\n",
      "\n",
      "3. **Cost explosion** — each iteration is an API call\n",
      "   - Fix: batch tools per iteration, reuse results, set lower max_iterations\n",
      "\n",
      "4. **No progress detection** — agent unsure if it's learning\n",
      "   - Fix: explicit memory (confidence score, finding list)\n",
      "\n",
      "5. **Context window overflow** — message history grows unbounded\n",
      "   - Fix: summarize old messages, store in database, use prompt caching (Phase 6)"
    ]
  },
